This paper deals with the problem of generating random bits from a finite state Markov chain, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the algorithm, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of algorithms and probability theory, which are relevant to the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
